metadata.name: waitwhut #1
metadata.description:
Odd moments. Odd situations. Odd people.

waitwhut is a series of 1/1 photographs designed to make the viewer say: wait, what the f%¨£ is going on here? Some of the pieces are strange, other awkward, but all of them make you want to investigate the story behind the photo. Why is there a baby cowboy roaming the desert? What's up with those killer trees? What is Jesus doing at this ladies' balcony? And most importantly: why was there a photographer present in these very odd situations?

Edition: 1/1

Contract: Manifold

About the artist: Sebastiaan Bedaux is a travel photographer and writer from Belgium. His work is published in magazines such as National Geographic Traveler, ELLE Belgium and Marie Claire Belgium. He has published 4 travel books.
